# File header: demonstrates comment support in the LTAC format.
# Second line of the file header.

# The Security package is the top-level entry point.
- Claim Security: The system is acceptably secure
  # Comment about Requirements at depth 1.
  - Claim ^Requirements
  # Comment about Design at depth 1.

  # Blank line above is absorbed into the group.
  - Claim ^Design

# Requirements: what the system must achieve.
- Claim Requirements: Security requirements are identified and met
  - Claim Confidentiality: Confidentiality is maintained
    # Evidence for confidentiality is at depth 2.
    - Evidence ConfEvidence: TLS configuration reviewed (tls.pdf)
  - Claim Integrity: Integrity is maintained

- Claim Design: Security is implemented in the design
# Trailing comment after the last package.
